label.value: transformation of host cell by virus

value.value: A virus-induced cellular transformation resulting in immortalized cells, or cells capable of indefinite replication.
The process in which a rRNA, ribosomal ribonucleic acid, is transported from the mitochondrial matrix into the cytosol.
The process in which a lrRNA, large subunit ribosomal ribonucleic acid, is transported from the mitochondrial matrix into the cytosol.
The process in which a srRNA, small subunit ribosomal ribonucleic acid, is transported from the mitochondrial matrix into the cytosol.
Any process in which mitochondrial RNA is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.
Any process in which mRNA is transported to, or maintained in, the oocyte pole plasm. An example of this is found in Drosophila melanogaster.
Any process in which mitochondrial ribosomal RNA is transported to, or maintained in, the oocyte pole plasm. An example of this is found in Drosophila melanogaster.
Any process in which mitochondrial large ribosomal RNA is transported to, or maintained in, the oocyte pole plasm. An example of this is found in Drosophila melanogaster.
Any process in which mitochondrial small ribosomal RNA is transported to, or maintained in, the oocyte pole plasm. An example of this is found in Drosophila melanogaster.
The specific behavior of an organism that is associated with reproduction.
The determination of sex and sexual phenotype in a female organism's germ line.
The determination of sex and sexual phenotype in a male organism's germ line.
The determination of sex and sexual phenotypes in a female organism's soma.
The determination of sex and sexual phenotypes in a male organism's soma.
Binding to a pyrimidine nucleotide, a pyrimidine nucleoside esterified with (ortho)phosphate.

Catalysis of the removal of damaged bases by cleaving the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the target damaged DNA base and the deoxyribose sugar. The reaction releases a free base and leaves an apurinic/apyrimidinic (AP) site.
Catalysis of the transfer of a myristoyl (CH3-[CH2]12-CO-) group to an acceptor molecule.
Catalysis of the reaction: an aromatic aldehyde + NAD+ + H2O = an aromatic acid + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: phenanthrol + X-SO3(-) = HX + phenanthrylsulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction: phenanthrol + glucose = phenanthryl-beta-D-glucopyranoside + H2O.
Catalysis of a monooxygenase reaction in which oxygen is incorporated into limonene.
Catalysis of the reaction: benzaldehyde + NAD(P)+ + H2O = benzoate + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: 6-hydroxynicotine + H2O + O2 = 1-(6-hydroxypyrid-3-yl)-4-(methylamino)butan-1-one + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction: a phenanthrene dioxide + H2O = a dihydrodiolphenanthrene.
Catalysis of the reaction: phenanthrene-9,10-oxide + H2O = trans-9,10-dihydrodiolphenanthrene.

label.value: hydrolase activity, acting on acid halide bonds, in C-halide compounds

value.value: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any acid halide bond in substances containing halogen atoms in organic linkage.
The formation of peptidyl-D-alanine, by either racemization or from peptidyl-L-serine.

definition.value: See also the biological process terms 'peptidyl-D-alanine racemization, direct ; GO:0019916' and 'peptidyl-D-alanine racemization via peptidyl-L-serine ; GO:0019917'.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: choline + 2 reduced ferredoxin + O2 + 2 H+ = betaine aldehyde hydrate + 2 oxidized ferredoxin + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: alpha-D-glucosamine 1-phosphate + acetyl-CoA = N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine 1-phosphate + CoA + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: protein N6-(4-aminobutyl)-L-lysine + donor-H2 + O2 = protein N6-((R)-4-amino-2-hydroxybutyl)-L-lysine + acceptor + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + 2'-deoxynucleoside = ADP + 2'-deoxynucleoside 5'-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: a thioglucoside + H2O = a thiol + a sugar.
Catalysis of the reaction: N6-dimethylallyladenine + acceptor + H2O = adenine + 3-methylbut-2-enal + reduced electron acceptor.

definition.value: Note that this term has a MetaCyc pathway reference as the pathway only has a single step.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + myo-inositol = ADP + 1D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate.

Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-pantolactone + NADP+ = 2-dehydropantolactone + NADPH + H+. The reaction is B-specific (i.e. the pro-S hydrogen is transferred from the 4-position of reduced nicotinamide cofactor) with respect to NADP+.
Catalysis of the reaction: glyoxylate + H2O + propanoyl-CoA = 2-hydroxyglutarate + CoA + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: 8-phospho-3-deoxy-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonate + H2O = 3-deoxy-D-manno-octulosonate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: ADP-sugar + H2O = AMP + sugar 1-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 4-aminobutanal + NAD+ + H2O = 4-aminobutanoate + NADH + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-arabinose 5-phosphate = D-ribulose 5-phosphate + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-1-aminopropan-2-ol + NAD+ = aminoacetone + H+ + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-cysteine + H2O = sulfide + NH3 + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 3-chloro-D-alanine + H2O = pyruvate + chloride + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + D-ribulose = ADP + D-ribulose 5-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-galactose + NAD+ = D-galactono-1,4-lactone + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: acetoin + NAD+ = diacetyl + NADH + H+. This reaction is catalyzed in the reverse direction.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 glutathione + protein-disulfide = glutathione disulfide+ protein-dithiol.
Catalysis of the reaction: A + glycolate = AH(2) + glyoxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-3-(imidazol-5-yl)lactate + NADP+ = 3-(imidazol-5-yl)pyruvate + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of alpha-(1,6)-D-glucosidic branch linkages in glycogen, amylopectin and their beta-limits dextrins.
